# â”€â”€ STEP 4b: Affiliate vanity links â€” proxy to the Render backend â”€
#
# /ref/:slug is an Express route on Render, not a Netlify page.
# Without this rule, uyehtech.com/ref/somecreator 404s on Netlify â€”
# it never reaches the backend at all.
#
# 301 = simple redirect: browser briefly shows the Render domain, then
# Render's own res.redirect() bounces it again to /marketplace/?ref=CODE
# on uyehtech.com. Two hops, but simple and reliable.
#
# If you'd rather the address bar never shows the Render domain, change
# 301 to 200 to make Netlify reverse-proxy it instead (keeps uyehtech.com
# in the bar throughout) â€” test this option before relying on it, proxy
# behavior with upstream redirects can be inconsistent across Netlify plans.

#   /marketplace/STORE_SLUG/
#     ↑ storeUrl from GET /api/creator/me (trailing slash always present)
#
#   /marketplace/STORE_SLUG/?product=PRODUCT_ID&ref=AFFILIATE_CODE
#     ↑ affiliateLink for product-specific links (lines 17430, 17469)
#
#   /marketplace/STORE_SLUG/?product=ID&ref=CODE&utm_campaign=X
#     ↑ same + campaign UTM (line 17474 generate route)
#
#   /marketplace/STORE_SLUG/?product=ID&ref=CODE&utm_source=X&utm_medium=Y
#     ↑ same + source/medium UTM params
#
/ref/*            https://uyehtechbackend.onrender.com/ref/:splat   301

